  "notes": "Game Changers are legal Commander cards that strongly shape what kind of game a deck creates. They are not banned. Brackets 1 and 2 expect zero. Bracket 3 allows up to 3. Brackets 4 and 5 allow any. Categories are descriptive, not gating: a card may belong to more than one play pattern but is filed under its loudest one for UI grouping.",
  "categories": {
    "fast_mana": "Cheap or free mana acceleration that creates large early-turn power gaps.",
    "tutor": "Efficient tutors that consistently find best-in-class answers or win pieces.",
    "engine": "Resource engines that snowball card or mana advantage when unanswered.",
    "prison": "Pieces that constrain opponents' ability to play normally.",
    "finisher": "Compact game-ending or storm-enabling effects.",
    "protection": "Free or near-free interaction and protection that warps the stack.",
    "land": "Lands strong enough to set the bracket on their own.",
    "commander": "Commanders whose presence changes the texture of the game.",
    "reset": "Effects that reset or warp the table in ways many players want to opt into knowingly."
  },
